    <stitle>CAB: 4100, 4200, 4300 AND 4400 MODELS - DESCRIPTION - ELECTRIC WINDSHIELD WIPERS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ELECTRIC WINDSHIELD WIPERS</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1602604">Figure 4</hotlnk>
            for Items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <para>The windshield wiper system consists of a single unitized 12 volt electric wiper motor (Item 1) that
            operates the wiper arms (Item 2) through wiper linkage (Item 3). The motor has two speeds (low and high),
            and a park position which is controlled by a three-position switch.
        </para>
        <para>Since the electric wiper motor is of unitized construction, there is no need for motor rebuild or
            adjustments. There are no serviceable parts; the complete assembly is replaced.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1602604" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg16/g1602603.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="392px"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Electric Windshield Wipers</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. ELECTRIC WIPER MOTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. WIPER ARM</callout1>
                <callout1>3. WIPER LINKAGE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
